sd.PT_NAME: Reaction to previous exposure to any vaccine
sd.LLT_NAME: Reaction to previous exposure to any vaccine

freetext.SYMPTOMS_DESCRIPTION: Joint pain in jaws, hips, fingers, thumbs, toes. No muscle pain. It started about a week after the first shot. The pain peaked 2 wks. after shot and continues. The same thing happened to me after the 1st shinges shot and from all statins.
Neuropathy in feet. Joint pain in most joints continues since first vaccine. Muscle pain occured after 2nd dose. A Medrol Pack started one week after the 2nd dose greatly reduced the joint pain.

Ten days plus of joint pain in fingers, toes, hips, pelvis, ankles and jaws cotinues and now includes muscle pain too.  I use Advil around the clock but it doesn't help much. I can't get any relief, sleeping is impossible.

checkin_info.SYSTEMIC_REACTION: Rash, not including the immediate area around the injection site
